"48:11:28" : {s: 48, a: 11, w: 28, r: "", t: "أَوْ", l: "أَو", lc: 280, tl: "aw", lb: "অথবা",e: "or", b: "অথবা", f: 263, rm: ""},
"48:11:29" : {s: 48, a: 11, w: 29, r: "رود", t: "أَرَادَ", l: "أَرَادَ", lc: 139, tl: "arāda", lb: "ইচ্ছা করা",e: "He intends", b: "চেয়েছেন", f: 18, rm: "to seek, ask a thing gently, search (for food), go to and fro in a pasture, go round about. iradatun - will, free will. mirwad - axle of a pully. rawada - to long after, desire, seduce, entice, seduce against the will (with an) as in 12:126. yuridu - he wishes, intends. It is used as an auxiliary verb as in 18:77. The word iradah is used for power and capacity with reference to subjugation as well as to option and choice. ruwaidan - for a little while, go gently (according to some grammarians the word is a diminutive form of which verbal noun is not in use, it is used as sing. plu. f. m.)."},
"48:11:30" : {s: 48, a: 11, w: 30, r: "", t: "بِكُمْ", l: "", lc: 3307, tl: "bikum", lb: "",e: "for you", b: "তোমাদের জন্য", f: 27, rm: ""},
